  <div class="amber-rule"></div>
  <div class="h-eyebrow">The reason this exists</div>

  <div class="h-flex">
    <div>
      <h1 class="h-title">Why.</h1>
      <p class="h-sub">The operating model exists so anyone can test at home, get a clear result, and take action with confidence: <strong>whether they self-screened with the NHS App (Abdul, CVKM), a clinician requested it (Mark, PSA-AS) or their GP arranged it as routine monitoring (Layla, iron deficiency anaemia)</strong>. It resolves into one shape: a single shared purpose at the top, the actors who serve it, and the one economic rule that holds them together.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="h-portrait" style="display:flex;gap:10px;justify-content:center;">
      <div style="text-align:center;">
        <img src="Assets/Personas/abdul.png" alt="Abdul" style="width:120px;height:auto;display:block;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#C9A227;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:6px;">Abdul &middot; CVKM</div>
        <div style="font-size:9.5px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-top:1px;">Patient-init &middot; screening</div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center;">
        <img src="Assets/Personas/mark.png" alt="Mark" style="width:120px;height:auto;display:block;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#C9A227;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:6px;">Mark &middot; PSA-AS</div>
        <div style="font-size:9.5px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-top:1px;">Clinician-init</div>
      </div>
      <div style="text-align:center;">
        <img src="Assets/Personas/layla.png" alt="Layla" style="width:120px;height:auto;display:block;">
        <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#C9A227;text-transform:uppercase;margin-top:6px;">Layla &middot; iron deficiency anaemia</div>
        <div style="font-size:9.5px;color:var(--text-muted);margin-top:1px;">GP-init</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

<div class="spine-section" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#003087,#005EB8);color:#fff;border-radius:18px;padding:34px 38px;margin:36px 0 12px;box-shadow:0 14px 40px rgba(0,48,135,0.20);">
    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:2px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">The spine of the model</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:32px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.7px;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:14px;">Orchestrate the market. Do not supply it.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.95);max-width:880px;margin-bottom:18px;">NHSE is the matchmaker, the market-maker, the bridge between innovation and care. It sets the standards, manages the framework, builds the integrations and runs the platform. It does not sign local contracts, own the billing, deliver care, or pick a single supplier. Anything that pulls NHSE into being the supplier breaks the 2030 vision.</p>
    <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.14);border:1.5px solid #FFB91D;border-radius:14px;padding:22px 26px;margin-top:14px;">
      <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px;">North Star &middot; the purpose every actor serves</div>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:14px;align-items:flex-start;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div style="display:flex;flex-shrink:0;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/abdul.png" alt="Abdul" title="Abdul" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/mark.png" alt="Mark" title="Mark" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;margin-left:-12px;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/layla.png" alt="Layla" title="Layla" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;margin-left:-12px;">
          <img src="Assets/Personas/sean.png" alt="Sean" title="Sean" style="width:50px;height:50px;border-radius:50%;border:2.5px solid #FFB91D;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;margin-left:-12px;">
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:280px;">
          <div style="font-size:23px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.18;margin-bottom:9px;letter-spacing:-0.4px;">Better outcomes, reached fairly.</div>
          <div style="font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);max-width:840px;">Above every actor's north star sits one shared end: <strong style="color:#fff;">better access</strong> for the people a clinic-based system leaves behind, <strong style="color:#fff;">earlier detection</strong> at population scale, and <strong style="color:#fff;">fairer outcomes</strong> by closing the gap in who gets tested and when. The faces above are not the audience for this model. They are its purpose. Easy buying, easy onboarding and an orchestrating centre are the means. This is the end every one of them serves, and the one the patient never has to ask for.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.4px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.62);margin:18px 0 4px;text-transform:uppercase;">And for each actor, that resolves into one north star, one reason to be in, and one economic truth</div>
    <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(210px,1fr));gap:14px;margin-top:8px;">
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/sarah.png" alt="Sarah" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #FFD66B;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;">Commissioner</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Easy buying.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">Ready-made, not bespoke: find it, decide it's right, onboard, go live.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The money:</strong> saves, or gets more for the same money, at pathway level.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/joe.png" alt="Joe" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #5BC093;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#5BC093;text-transform:uppercase;">Supplier</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Easy onboarding.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">A clean, repeatable route to volume: onboard once, reuse across conditions.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The money:</strong> sell across conditions with no assurance burden per deployment.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/aisha.png" alt="Aisha" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #C9A0E3;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#C9A0E3;text-transform:uppercase;">Clinician</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Pathway fit.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">The test arrives inside the pathway I already run, not as a second screen.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The value:</strong> clinic time concentrates where it is needed; routine work leaves the room.</div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:18px 20px;">
        <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:10px;margin-bottom:10px;"><img src="Assets/Personas/priya.png" alt="Priya" style="width:38px;height:38px;border-radius:50%;border:2px solid #7EC8E3;object-fit:cover;object-position:top center;background:#fff;flex-shrink:0;"><div style="font-size:10px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#7EC8E3;text-transform:uppercase;">The centre</div></div>
        <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:800;color:#fff;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:8px;">Matchmaker, not counterparty.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11.5px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.88);margin-bottom:7px;">Set the standards, run the platform, hold the 2030 vision. Never the supplier.</div>
        <div style="font-size:11px;line-height:1.5;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.18);padding-top:7px;"><strong style="color:#fff;">The money:</strong> funded sustainably through orchestration, not through supply.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

    <div style="margin:30px 0 0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1B3A6B,#003087);border-radius:14px;padding:24px 30px;color:#fff;box-shadow:0 10px 30px rgba(0,48,135,0.18);">
      <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">The one rule that binds them</div>
      <div style="font-size:20px;font-weight:900;letter-spacing:-0.3px;line-height:1.25;margin-bottom:10px;">All four north stars have to hold at the same time.</div>
      <div style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);max-width:880px;">The supplier makes money. The commissioner saves money or gets more for the same money. The clinician's time goes where it is needed. The centre is funded through orchestration, never as the supplier. These are not competing interests to be traded off. They are simultaneous conditions: <strong style="color:#fff;">if any one of them fails, the platform fails</strong>, and the patient purpose at the top goes unmet. The model's job is to make all four true at once.</div>
    </div>

  <div class="pathway-econ-callout" style="margin:36px 0 0;background:#FFF9EC;border:1px solid #F0DCA0;border-left:6px solid #C9A227;border-radius:12px;padding:24px 28px;">
    <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:2px;color:#9A6700;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:8px;">Where the economics actually resolves</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:22px;font-weight:800;color:#003087;letter-spacing:-0.4px;line-height:1.2;margin-bottom:12px;">The commissioner case lands at pathway level, not test level.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;color:#4C6272;margin:0 0 10px;">The economics lens above is necessary, not sufficient. In live commissioning, the cost of a new test and the saving it produces sit on different budget lines. The new test cost lands with one budget holder; the freed-up clinic capacity, the avoided onward referral and the workforce time recovered land with others. A commissioner already paying for cheaper venepuncture cannot fund the switch out of test economics alone. It reads as a cost pressure on top of an existing line.</p>
    <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.7;color:#4C6272;margin:0;">The model only delivers at scale when the test sits inside a pathway and the pathway carries the economics. Best-practice tariffs at pathway level, costed against the end-to-end condition pathway, not against the test as a component. Tariff articulation itself sits outside this operating model. The operating model&apos;s job is to make the dependency explicit: <strong>configurations only land where the commissioner has a viable funding route at the pathway level.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <div class="strat-section">
    <div class="strat-eyebrow">What we're trying to figure out at a strategic level</div>
    <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#003087,#005EB8);border:2px solid #FFB91D;border-radius:14px;padding:22px 26px;margin-top:18px;">
      <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.8px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">Supplier-onboarding north star &middot; the structural commitment</div>
      <div style="font-size:23px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.18;margin-bottom:10px;letter-spacing:-0.4px;">Assure once. Reuse nationally.</div>
      <div style="font-size:13.5px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);max-width:880px;">A supplier admitted to the framework is admitted once. The clinical safety case, the IG package and the lab assurance are then portable across every commissioner who calls them off. The local body acts as the deployment authority &mdash; not as a re-assurer. The published artefact stack (templates for DSA, DPIA, DCB0160, clinical safety case starter) is the carrier of the assurance, not the local team. The centre&apos;s job is the upstream assurance; the local job is administering the deployment, not redoing the work.</div>
    </div>
    <h2 class="strat-title">Three strategic questions.</h2>
    <p class="strat-intro">Cross-cutting questions that <strong>apply to every product</strong>, not just to one stage or one pathway. The three lenses above frame why the model exists. These three frame what is genuinely hard about making it work.</p>
    <div class="strat-grid">
      <div class="strat-q">
        <div class="strat-q-num">Question 01</div>
        <div class="strat-q-h">Route to market</div>
        <div class="strat-q-body">What is the best route to market? How does the centre create a market for each product so that demand and supply meet in a way that scales?</div>
      </div>
      <div class="strat-q">
        <div class="strat-q-num">Question 02</div>
        <div class="strat-q-h">Commercial viability</div>
        <div class="strat-q-body">How is this made attractive to commissioners, financially viable for suppliers, and demonstrably value for money for the NHS, all at the same time?</div>
      </div>
      <div class="strat-q">
        <div class="strat-q-num">Question 03</div>
        <div class="strat-q-h">Supply chain at scale</div>
        <div class="strat-q-body">How is a supply chain built that can handle different use cases, different initiation patterns, and grow with volume without fragmenting?</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="precedent-section" style="background:#F4F8FC; border:1px solid #D5E8F0; border-radius:14px; padding:28px 32px; margin:36px 0;">
    <div style="font-size:11px; font-weight:800; letter-spacing:1.6px; color:#005EB8; text-transform:uppercase;">The shape of the model is not new</div>
    <h2 style="font-size:22px; font-weight:800; color:#003087; margin:8px 0 14px; letter-spacing:-0.3px;">Same shape as existing NHS national models.</h2>
    <p style="font-size:14px; line-height:1.7; color:#3C4856; margin:0;">The model is not inventing a new way of doing things. It is taking proven NHS national mechanics and applying them to home testing. <strong>Accreditation</strong> sits with established bodies that already do it: CQC for provider quality, the National Cancer Board, GIRFT or the relevant Royal College depending on the test. <strong>Listing</strong> works the way the National Choice Framework already lists eligible providers for elective care. <strong>Access</strong> works the way ERS already gives clinicians a national digital route to those providers. NHSE is the platform that brings the three together for home testing; it is not the body that decides whether a test is clinically safe. That sits where it sits today. <strong>Same shape, new application.</strong></p>
  </div>

  
  <div class="dot-section" style="margin:36px 0 0;">
    <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#003087,#005EB8);border-radius:18px;padding:34px 38px;color:#fff;box-shadow:0 14px 40px rgba(0,48,135,0.20);">
      <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:2px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.78);text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">Direction of travel</div>
      <h2 style="font-size:32px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;letter-spacing:-0.7px;line-height:1.1;margin-bottom:14px;">From launch to self-sustaining.</h2>
      <p style="font-size:15.5px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.95);max-width:880px;margin-bottom:24px;">The orchestrator stance holds throughout. What changes between launch and 2030 is how the operating envelope is funded, not who is the buyer. Three time bands, one direction.</p>
      <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:14px;">
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:20px 22px;">
          <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">Day 1 &middot; launch through 2026/27</div>
          <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.22;margin-bottom:10px;letter-spacing:-0.3px;">Commissioner-to-supplier direct.</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);line-height:1.6;">Commissioners hold the budget and pay suppliers directly. NHSE runs the framework, the standards and the platform. No payment flows pass through NHSE. This is the position that gets HIV live, lands the first PSA AS configurations and gives the platform a volume base.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:20px 22px;">
          <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">Year 2/3 &middot; transition begins</div>
          <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.22;margin-bottom:10px;letter-spacing:-0.3px;">The platform-fee model lands.</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);line-height:1.6;">Suppliers admitted to the framework pay a Procurement Act compliant management fee on call-off only, with transparent reinvestment. NHS Supply Chain runs a published 1% mechanism as the precedent. NHSE moves from grant-funded to part-funded by the activity it has enabled. Trigger conditions are approved-list maturity and sustainable call-off volume.</div>
        </div>
        <div style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.22);border-radius:12px;padding:20px 22px;">
          <div style="font-size:10.5px;font-weight:800;letter-spacing:1.6px;color:#FFD66B;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:10px;">2030 &middot; destination</div>
          <div style="font-size:17px;font-weight:900;color:#fff;line-height:1.22;margin-bottom:10px;letter-spacing:-0.3px;">Self-sustaining.</div>
          <div style="font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);line-height:1.6;">HomeTest pays for itself. The framework fee plus accountable savings credited to the system cover the operating envelope. The model is an active profit centre in its own books, with the buyer still local. The orchestrator role does not change; the funding mechanism does.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="margin-top:22px;padding-top:18px;border-top:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.20);font-size:13.5px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.92);line-height:1.65;">
        <strong style="color:#FFD66B;">Both states are true at the same time.</strong> The Day 1 stance is what makes 2030 reachable. The platform fee is what makes the orchestrator role durable past grant funding. The model evolves through the three time bands without breaking either principle.
      </div>
